### You are given two sorted arrays, A and B, and A has a large enough buffer at the end to hold B. Write a method to merge B into A in sorted order. 

def merge(nums1, m, nums2, n):
    while m > 0 and n > 0:
        if nums1[m-1] >= nums2[n-1]:
            nums1[m+n-1] = nums1[m-1]You are given two sorted arrays, A and B, and A has a large enough buffer at the end to hold B. Write a method to merge B into A in sorted order
            m = m - 1
        else:
            nums1[m+n-1] = nums2[n-1]
            n = n - 1
    if n > 0:
        nums1[:n] = nums2[:n]
